ApproachBody.description: Written in Supercruise, and distance from planet drops to within the 'Orbital Cruise' zone.

AsteroidCracked.description: Written when the player has broken up a "Motherlode" asteroid for mining.

Retreat.description: Indicates if requested for exit from combat zone.

Bounty.description: Written when player is awarded a bounty for a kill.

Faction.description: Faction paying the bounty (when bounty is for a skimmer).

Reward.description: The reward (when bounty is for a skimmer).

Rewards.description: An array of faction names and the reward values, as the target can have multiple bounties per faction.

SharedWithOthers.description: If credit for the kill is shared with other players this has the number of other players involved.

Target.description: Type of ship or target (if skimmer).

BuyExplorationData.description: Written when buying system data via the galaxy map.

CapShipBond.description: Written when the player has been rewarded for a capital ship combat.

Cargo.description:
Written slightly later in startup after missions are initialized so cargo coming from an abandoned delivery mission
can be detected.

The first Cargo event in the file will contain the full inventory.

A simple event (with no Inventory property) is written to the main journal file when the cargo file is updated.

Inventory.description: Array of cargo. Not set when Cargo.json file was written instead.

MissionID.description: ID of the mission the item belongs to.

Stolen.description: How many of the items are stolen.

CarrierFinance.description: Change to tax rate or reserve

ClearSavedGame.description: Written when player resets the game.

CodexEntry.description: Written when a new discovery is added to the Codex.

NearestDestination.description: Added if within 50km of a location listed in the navigation panel.

Commander.description: Written at start of the game loading process.

DiscoveryScan.description:
Written when using the discovery scanner, and new body discoveries are displayed in the cockpit info window.
Note you can get two or three of these in a row, where some bodies are discovered by the automatic passive scan,
before the active scan is complete.

Docked.description:
Written when landing at landing pad in a space station, output, or surface settlement.

The "anonymous docking" protocol comes into effect if you're either Wanted (ie have a local bounty)
or have an ActiveFine.

ActiveFine.description: True if any fine is active.

CockpitBreach.description: True if landing with breached cockpit.

StarSystem.description: The name of the start system.

Wanted.description: True if docking when wanted locally.

DockingCancelled.description: Written when the player cancels a docking request.

DockingDenied.description: Written when the station denies a docking request.

DockingGranted.description: Written when a docking request is granted.

DockingRequested.description: Written when the player requests a docking at a station.

DockingTimeout.description: Written when a docking request has timed out.

EngineerApply.description: This event is obsolete and no longer written since ED v3.0.

EscapeInterdiction.description: Written when player has escaped interdiction.

FCMaterials.description:
Written when trading with a Fleet Carrier Bartender for materials, a file is written with the price list.
Similar to the Shipyard and Cargo events, a brief entry is written in the journal.

FSDJump.description: Written when jumping from one star to another.

Factions.description: Info for the local minor factions.

Powers.description: Names of any powers contesting the system, or the name of the controlling power.

StarPos.description: Star position as array (x, y, z) in light years.

FSDTarget.description:
Written when selecting a star system to jump to.

Note, when following a multi-jump route, this will typically appear for the next star, during a jump, ie
after "StartJump" but before the "FSDJump"

FSSAllBodiesFound.description: Written after having identified all bodies in the system.

FSSDiscoveryScan.description: Written when performing a full system scan ("Honk")

BodyCount.description: Number of stellar bodies in system.

Progress.description: A value in range 0-1 showing how completely the system has been scanned.

FSSSignalDiscovered.description: Written when zooming in on a signal using the FSS scanner.

IsStation.description: True if it is a station.

SpawningState.description: The BGS state that triggered this event, if relevant.

TimeRemaining.description: Remaining lifetime in seconds, if relevant

FactionKillBond.description: Written when player is rewarded for taking part in a combat zone.

FighterDestroyed.description: Written when a ship-launched fighter is destroyed.

Fileheader.description:
The heading entry is added at the beginning of every file.

The first event in a new journal file. If the play session goes on a long time, and the journal gets very large,
the file will be closed and a new file is started with an increased part number. See also the {@link Continued}
event.

Odyssey.description: True when odyssey, false if other version.

gameversion.description: Which version of the game produced the log (will indicate if beta).

HeatDamage.description: When taking damage due to overheating.

HullDamage.description: Written when hull health drops below a threshold (20% steps).

PlayerPilot.description: True if player is piloting the ship/fighter taking damage.

Interdicted.description: Written when player was interdicted by player or NPC.

Power.description: The power if NPC working for one.

Submitted.description: Whether player submitted to the interdiction.

Interdiction.description: Written when player has (attempted to) interdict another player or NPC.

Power.description: Power (if NPC working for a power).

LeaveBody.description: Written when flying away from a planet and distance increases above the "Orbital Cruise" altitude.

Liftoff.description: Written when taking off from planet surface.

PlayerControlled.description: False if ship dismissed when player is in SRV, true if player is taking off.

LoadGame.description: Written at startup when loading from main menu into the game.

Group.description: Name of the group (if in a group.

ShipID.description: The ID of the current ship.

StartDead.description: True if starting dead. See {@link Resurrect}.

Loadout.description:
Written at startup when loading from main menu, when switching ships, after changing the ship in outfitting or
when docking SRV back in mothership.

MaxJumpRange.description: Maximum jump range based on zero cargo, and just enough fuel for 1 jump.

AmmoInClip.description: For a passenger cabin, holds the number of places in the cabin.

EngineerBlueprint.description: Replaced by Engineering object in newer version.

EngineerLevel.description: Replaced by Engineering object in newer version.

BlueprintID.description: The ID of the applied blueprint.

BlueprintName.description: The name of the applied blueprint.

ExperimentalEffect_Localised.description: Localised name of applied experimental effect.

On.description: Indicates if module is on or off.

UnladenMass.description: Mass of hull and modules, excludes fuel and cargo.

Location.description: Written at startup or when being resurrected at a station.

Powers.description: Names of any powers contesting the system, or the name of the controlling power.

StarPos.description: Star position as array (x, y, z) in light years.

MaterialDiscovered.description: Written when a new material is discovered.

Materials.description:
Written at startup when loading from main menu into the game. Indicates the number of materials in the player's
inventory.

MissionAccepted.description: Accept some kill missions to verify

Missions.description: The player's missions. Written at startup.

MultiSellExplorationData.description: Written when selling exploration data in Cartographics, a page at a time.

NavBeaconScan.description:
Written when scanning a navigation beacon, before the scan data for all the bodies in the system is written into
the journal.

NavRoute.description:
When plotting a multi-star route, the file NavRoute.json is written in the same directory as the journal, with a
list of stars along that route.

NavRouteClear.description: When the current plotted nav route is cleared.

NewCommander.description: Written when creating a new commander.

Outfitting.description: Written when accessing the outfitting menu.

PVPKill.description: Written when this player has killed another player.

Passengers.description: List of passengers in the ship. Written at startup when loading the saved game file.

Powerplay.description: Written at startup if player has pledged to a power.

CQC.description: Percent progress to next CQC rank.

Combat.description: Percent progress to next combat rank.

Empire.description: Percent progress to next empire rank.

Exobiologist.description: Percent progress to next exobiologist rank.

Explore.description: Percent progress to next exploration rank.

Federation.description: Percent progress to next federation rank.

Soldier.description: Percent progress to next soldier rank.

Trade.description: Percent progress to next trade rank.

Reputation.description:
Player's reputation on a scale of -100 to +100 with the superpowers. Written at startup after {@link Rank} and
{@link Progress}.

Thresholds:

* -100 to -90: Hostile
*  -90 to -35: Unfriendly
*  -35 to   4: Neutral
*    4 to  35: Cordial
*   35 to  90: Friendly
*   90 to 100: Allied

SAAScanComplete.description: Written after using the Surface Area Analysis scanner.

SAASignalsFound.description: Written when using SAA scanner on a planet or rings.

SRVDestroyed.description: Written when the player's SRV is destroyed.

Scan.description:
Written on basic or detailed discovery scan of a star, planet or moon.

This is also generated when scanning a navigation beacon in a populated system, to record info
about all the bodies in the system

StellarMass.description: Mass as multiple of Sol's mass.

ScanBaryCentre.description:
Written when scanning a body of a binary pair. YOu will now get an event detailing the orbital parameters of their
barycenter.

Screenshot.description:
Written when a screenshot has been taken.

The latitude, longitude, altitude and heading will be included if on a planet or in low-altitude flight.

SellExplorationData.description: Written when selling exploration data in Cartographics.

TotalEarnings.description: Total credits received (including for example the 200% bonus if rank 5 with Li Yong Rui)

SellShipOnRebuy.description: TODO Verify by getting destroyed and selling the ship.

ShieldState.description: Written when shields are disabled in combat, or recharged.

ShieldsUp.description: false when disabled, true when restored.

ShipLocker.description:
Lists the contents of the ship locker, eg at startup. The full list is written into the journal at startup
(if in a ship) and when boarding a ship. For other updates the ship locker has to be watched separately.

ShipTargeted.description:
Written when the current player selects a new target.

The amount of data written depends on the extent to which the target ship has been scanned

Power.description: The power a scanned player is aligned to. Only set when player is also aligned to a power.

Shipyard.description: Written when accessing shipyard in a station.

ShipyardBuy.description: Verify by buying a new ship and selling the current one the same time.

ShipyardSwap.description: TODO Verify by swapping ship and selling the old one at the same time.

StartJump.description: Written at the start of a hyperspace or supercruise jump (start of countdown)

StarClass.description: Star type (Only for a hyperspace jump)

StarSystem.description: Name of destination system (for a hyperspace jump)

Statistics.description:
The information displayed in the statistics panel on the right side of the cockpit. Written at startup.

Note: Times are in seconds.

StoredModules.description: TODO Revalidate? Some mismatches between Log and API doc

SupercruiseEntry.description: Written when entering supercruise from normal space.

SupercruiseExit.description: Written when leaving supercruise for normal space.

Touchdown.description: Written when landing on a planet surface.

NearestDestination.description: Included if within 50 km of a location listed in the nav panel.

PlayerControlled.description: False if ship was recalled from SRV, true if player is landing.

UnderAttack.description: Written when under fire (same time as the Under Attack voice message).

Undocked.description: Written when liftoff from a landing pad in a station, outpost or settlement.

description: Union type of all existing journal event types.
